[49m[39m  62, 62[0m:[39m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Glue: ~$0.44/DPU-hour (feature assembly + trajectory computation ~2-4 DPU-hours per run for 500K patients). SageMaker batch transform: ~$0.05/hour for ml.m5.xlarge (scoring 500K patients takes ~30 min). S3 storage: ~$0.023/GB/month. DynamoDB: on-demand pricing, ~$1.25 per million writes. Total: ~$50-150 per monthly scoring cycle for a 500K-member population. |
[0m[49m[39m  63, 63[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IAM role isolation per pipeline phase.** Do not use a single IAM role with broad permissions across the entire pipeline. Each phase should use a dedicated role scoped to the specific resource ARNs it needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Glue feature assembly role:** `s3:GetObject` on source data buckets + `s3:PutObject` on the feature store prefix only. No DynamoDB, no EventBridge, no SageMaker access.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **SageMaker batch transform role:** `s3:GetObject` on the feature store prefix + `s3:PutObject` on the score history prefix only. No DynamoDB, no SNS access.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Glue trajectory computation role:** `s3:GetObject` on the score history prefix + `s3:PutObject` on the trajectory results prefix only.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Lambda detection/routing role:** `dynamodb:PutItem` and `dynamodb:UpdateItem` on the risk state table + `events:PutEvents` on the specific event bus ARN. No S3 write access, no SageMaker access.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This limits the blast radius if any single component is compromised. A vulnerability in the Lambda detection function cannot be used to read raw clinical data from the source buckets, because that role simply doesn't have those permissions.
